# Node Kind

## Definition

A Node Kind describes the semantic category of a Node.

## Specification

Every Node MUST declare exactly one Kind.

The declared Kind MUST exist in the Schema.

The Kind determines which Edge types are valid for the Node.

A Kind SHOULD describe the purpose of the knowledge, not its storage location.

## Example

```
kind: requirement
```
